            <simpara>GT <replaceable role="entity">version</replaceable> release manuals are divided
                        into the following areas:</simpara>
            <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                                    <simpara>
                                                <emphasis role="strong">
                                                  <olink targetdoc="data">Data Management
                                                  Components</olink>
                                                </emphasis>
                                    </simpara>
                                    <simpara>Data management tools are concerned with the location,
                                                transfer, and management of distributed data. GT5
                                                provides various basic tools, including GridFTP for
                                                high-performance and reliable data transport, and
                                                RLS for maintaining location information for
                                                replicated files.</simpara>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                                    <simpara>
                                                <emphasis role="strong">
                                                  <olink targetdoc="execution">Execution (Jobs)
                                                  Management Components</olink>
                                                </emphasis>
                                    </simpara>
                                    <simpara>Execution management refers to the
                                                initiation, monitoring, management, scheduling,
                                                and/or coordination of remote computations. GT5
                                                supports the Grid Resource Allocation and Management
                                                (GRAM5) interface as a basic mechanism for these
                                                purposes.</simpara>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                                    <simpara>
                                                <emphasis role="strong">
                                                  <olink targetdoc="security">Security
                                                  Components</olink>
                                                </emphasis>
                                    </simpara>
                                    <simpara>These components establish the identity of users or
                                                services (authentication), protect communications,
                                                and determine who is allowed to perform what actions
                                                (authorization), as well as manage user
                                                credentials.</simpara>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                                    <simpara>
                                                <emphasis role="strong">
                                                  <olink targetdoc="common">Common Runtime
                                                  Components</olink>
                                                </emphasis>
                                    </simpara>
                                    <simpara>These components include a set of C Common libraries
                                                needed for building grid infrastructure and XIO, a
                                                sophisticated and extensible I/O library suitable
                                                for the dynamic needs of grid
                                                applications.</simpara>
                        </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
